Documentation of Testing and Debugging Process:

Completed laboratory safety training, understanding protocols for handling electronic components and tools.

Monitor temperature of voltage regulators during testing to prevent overheating.
Ensure all connections in the breadboard setup are secure to avoid intermittent faults.
Analysis and Proposed Solutions for Debugging Problems:

Addressed potential overheating by verifying that the input voltage does not exceed the maximum voltage difference as per LM1117 specifications.
Proposed using heat sinks for voltage regulators if overheating persists during prolonged use.

Planned to measure voltage regulation under varying loads to ensure stability across different operating conditions.
