Outlined the Subsystem Requirements section, detailing specifications for the Car System and Remote System.





Date: September 3, 2024
Objective: Finalize Project Proposal
Record:

Main Ideas from Project Proposal:
Consolidated the project goals and methodologies, emphasizing the integration of mechanical and electronic subsystems to achieve seamless item retrieval and transportation.

Included references to datasheets and component manuals for the TB6612 motor driver and LM1117 voltage regulator.
Reviewed additional academic papers on robotic arm control and remote system integration for enhanced design insights.
Diagrams and Schematics:

Updated the subsystem diagrams to include detailed connections between the microcontroller, motor drivers, and voltage regulators.

Design Problems and Decisions:

Microcontroller Integration: Decided to use the ESP32-S3's dual-core processing capabilities to handle simultaneous control of motors and camera data processing.
Remote Interface Design: Chose to implement a user-friendly Android application interface with joysticks and switches for intuitive control.
Equations and Formulas:
Documentation of Testing and Debugging Process:

Conducted initial tests on the breadboard setup to verify voltage outputs from the LM1117 regulators.
Documented voltage readings and confirmed they matched expected values within the tolerance range.
Important Notes for Debugging:

Ensure resistor values are precise to achieve accurate voltage regulation.
Double-check connections on the breadboard to prevent short circuits.
Analysis and Proposed Solutions for Debugging Problems:

Noted slight discrepancies in voltage outputs due to resistor tolerances and planned to use precision resistors for higher accuracy in the final PCB design.
Documentation of New Tests:

Scheduled load tests to evaluate voltage stability under different current draws, simulating real-world operating conditions.
Documentation of Final Performance Tests and Design Verification:

Planned comprehensive testing of the power subsystem once integrated into the PCB to ensure reliable performance.
Topic Outlines for Reports:

Developed outlines for the Design Review and Design Alternatives sections, preparing to discuss potential issues and solutions.
